automock
========
Build with mock at one command

Requirements to use automock:
1. .spec file and source files;
2. Source files should be in the same directory as the .spec file;
3. Installed mock.
Example tree in git:
.
├── libfprint-0.5.0.tar.xz
├── libfprint.spec
├── README.md
└── upeke2-add-147e-2020-IDs.patch

How to use automock from local:

Clean local repository:
$ /path/to/automock.sh clean
Update local repository:
$ /path/to/automock.sh update
Build package from git:
$ /path/to/automock.sh git://git_url/name.git?#hash version_of_fedora
Example to build libfprint to Fedora 19:
$ /home/repos/automock/automock.sh git://github.com/ignatenkobrain/libfprint.git?#830dc01abb45162e429bef59dc8a4c85a42be4ea 19

How to use automock from ssh:

Clean local repository:
ssh -p 2222 ignatenkobrain.asuscomm.com "automock.sh clean"
Update local repository:
ssh -p 2222 ignatenkobrain.asuscomm.com "automock.sh update"
Example to build libfprint to Fedora 19:
ssh -p 2222 ignatenkobrain.asuscomm.com "automock.sh git://github.com/ignatenkobrain/libfprint.git?#830dc01abb45162e429bef59dc8a4c85a42be4ea 19"

